# JAVA 8 — LAMBDA EXPRESSIONS COMPLETE THEORY

## 1. INTRODUCTION

Lambda Expression Java 8 me introduce hua tha.

Lambda Expression ka use Functional Interface ke single abstract method ka implementation concise form me provide karne ke liye kiya jata hai.

Simple definition:

Lambda Expression ek concise way hai Functional Interface ke single abstract method ka implementation likhne ka.

Example:

```java
() -> System.out.println("Hello");
```

Lambda Expression ko commonly anonymous function-like syntax kaha jata hai because:

- Iska apna method name nahi hota
- Implementation directly likha jata hai
- Parameters ho sakte hain
- Body ho sakti hai
- Value return kar sakta hai

Lekin Java me Lambda Expression independently exist nahi karta.

Lambda ko ek target type chahiye, aur wo target type generally Functional Interface hota hai.


============================================================
2. LAMBDA EXPRESSION KYU INTRODUCE HUA?
============================================================

Java 8 se pehle agar kisi interface ke method ka implementation dena hota tha, to commonly:

1. Separate Implementation Class
2. Anonymous Inner Class

use ki jati thi.


Example Interface:

```java
interface Greeting {

    void greet();

}
```


Traditional Implementation:

```java
class GreetingImpl implements Greeting {

    @Override
    public void greet() {

        System.out.println("Hello Vijay");

    }
}
```


Object:

```java
Greeting greeting = new GreetingImpl();

greeting.greet();
```


Problem:

Sirf ek chhote method ka implementation dene ke liye:

- Separate class
- implements keyword
- @Override
- Method declaration
- Extra boilerplate code

likhna pad raha tha.


============================================================
3. ANONYMOUS INNER CLASS
============================================================

Separate implementation class ko remove karne ke liye Anonymous Inner Class use kar sakte the.


Example:

```java
Greeting greeting = new Greeting() {

    @Override
    public void greet() {

        System.out.println("Hello Vijay");

    }

};
```


Separate class remove ho gayi.

Lekin code abhi bhi verbose tha.


Java 8 Lambda:

```java
Greeting greeting =
        () -> System.out.println("Hello Vijay");
```


Same purpose, much less boilerplate.


