7. FUNCTIONAL INTERFACE AND LAMBDA
============================================================

Lambda Expression Functional Interface ke saath use hota hai.


Functional Interface:

Aisa interface jisme exactly one abstract method hota hai.


Example:

```java
@FunctionalInterface
interface Greeting {

    void greet();

}
```


Lambda:

```java
Greeting greeting =
        () -> System.out.println("Hello");
```


Compiler ko pata hai ki:

```java
Greeting
```

ka single abstract method:

```java
void greet();
```

hai.


Isliye Lambda:

```java
() -> System.out.println("Hello");
```

`greet()` method ka implementation provide karta hai.


============================================================
8. TARGET TYPE
============================================================

Lambda Expression ka apna standalone type nahi hota.

Usko context se target type milta hai.


Example:

```java
Greeting greeting =
        () -> System.out.println("Hello");
```


Yahan target type hai:

```java
Greeting
```


Compiler check karta hai:

```text
Greeting
    ↓
Single Abstract Method
    ↓
void greet()
```


Lambda:

```java
() -> System.out.println("Hello")
```


match karta hai:

```java
void greet()
```


Isliye code valid hai.


Ye directly standalone statement ki tarah valid nahi:

```java
() -> System.out.println("Hello"); // ❌
```

Lambda ko target context chahiye.


