15. RETURN VALUE IN LAMBDA
============================================================

Interface:

```java
interface Calculator {

    int calculate(int a, int b);

}
```


Block body:

```java
Calculator add = (a, b) -> {

    return a + b;

};
```


Agar single expression hai:

```java
Calculator add =
        (a, b) -> a + b;
```


Yahan:

```java
return
```

likhne ki zarurat nahi.


Compiler automatically expression ka result return karta hai.


IMPORTANT:

Ye valid hai:

```java
(a, b) -> a + b
```


Ye bhi valid hai:

```java
(a, b) -> {
    return a + b;
}
```


Lekin ye invalid hai:

```java
(a, b) -> {
    a + b;
}
```

because block body me return value explicitly return karni hogi.


