17. LAMBDA EXPRESSION IS NOT A METHOD NAME
============================================================

Normal method:

```java
public int add(int a, int b) {

    return a + b;

}
```


Has:

- Access Modifier
- Return Type
- Method Name
- Parameters
- Body


Lambda:

```java
(a, b) -> a + b
```


Does not explicitly contain:

- Access Modifier
- Method Name
- Return Type


Compiler gets required information from the target Functional Interface.


