29. this KEYWORD IN LAMBDA
============================================================

Lambda Expression apna separate `this` context create nahi karta.

Lambda ke andar `this` enclosing class/object ko refer karta hai.


Ye Anonymous Inner Class se important difference hai.


Anonymous Inner Class:

`this`

anonymous class object ko refer kar sakta hai.


Lambda:

`this`

enclosing object ko refer karta hai.


============================================================
30. LAMBDA VS ANONYMOUS INNER CLASS
============================================================

LAMBDA:

- Concise syntax
- Functional Interface ke liye
- Separate `this` context nahi banata
- Functional-style behavior representation ke liye useful


ANONYMOUS INNER CLASS:

- More verbose
- Anonymous class instance create hota hai
- Apna `this` context hota hai
- Multiple methods implement/override karne wale suitable type scenarios me use ho sakta hai


IMPORTANT:

Lambda ko sirf Anonymous Inner Class ka textual shortcut samajhna completely accurate nahi hai.

Dono ke semantics me differences hain, especially:

```text
this
scope
implementation model
```


